<br /><br />2. Find out the industry keywords that are &amp;amp;quot;hot&amp;amp;quot; in your career field and put them into your Michigan Unemployment.
<br /><br />Why do this? Because more and more companies are using automated databases to store Michigan Unemployments. When they need to hire someone, they find potential candidates by utilizing key word phrases (sort of how you search on google using a keyword). If you are using the right keywords, your Michigan Unemployment will be included in the top contenders.
<br /><br />You can find the keyword phrases by searching monster.com or hotjobs.com for the job you want to apply to. Read several postings from all regions of the county and look for the qualifications and duties.
<br /><br />For instance, I looked up &amp;amp;quot;executive assistant&amp;amp;quot; and found the following phrases that seemed to be repeating:
<br /><br />&amp;amp;quot;Microsoft office proficient&amp;amp;quot;
